# How Blockchain Technology is Used in Tamil Nadu
(Main Focus: Real Estate Sector)
Tamil Nadu is one of the first Indian states to adopt blockchain for land and property management, mainly to prevent fraud, improve transparency, and secure ownership records.
## Why Blockchain is Needed in Real Estate (Problem First)
Before blockchain, real estate faced many issues:
Fake land documents
Multiple ownership claims
Manual record tampering
Lengthy property registration process
Corruption and middlemen
 Blockchain solves these problems by creating tamper-proof digital land records.
##How Blockchain Works in Tamil Nadu Real Estate
1ï¸.Digitization of Land Records
Property documents (sale deed, ownership details, survey numbers) are converted into digital records.
These records are stored on a blockchain network, not on a single server.
âœ” Once stored, data cannot be changed or deleted.
2.Immutable Property Ownership Records
Each land transaction creates a new block.
Every block is linked to the previous owner record.
